      <hedline>
        <hl1>Introduction</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Reader responses to special issue on first-year experiences of new New Yorkers and articles on young felon and 1980 presidential race (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Our special issue drew mail from former and native New Yorkers who said they, too, have stories to tell. A prosecutor offers a different perspective on a young felon. And prominent members of the 1980 Reagan campaign dispute that Gerald Ford was nearly chosen as ''co-president.''</p>
      </block>
